54 Section 4 of this bill creates the Account for the Security Operations Center in
55 the State General Fund to be administered by the Chief. Section 4 requires the
56 money in the Account to be used for the purposes of supporting and carrying out
57 the duties of the Security Operations Center. Section 4 also authorizes the Security
58 Operations Center to serve as a fiscal agent to pool federal grant funds for the
59 purposes of cybersecurity support and infrastructure development.
60 Section 5 of this bill requires the Security Operations Center to collaborate
61 with the Office of Information Security and Cyber Defense to enhance
62 communication and coordination of incident responses to cyber threats or
63 cyberattacks on information systems.
64 Section 6 of this bill requires the Security Operations Center to prepare and
65 submit an annual report to the Governor, Attorney General and the Director of the
66 Legislative Counsel Bureau for transmission to the Legislature that includes certain
67 information relating to the duties of the Security Operations Center.
68 Section 7 of this bill provides that the provisions of the Nevada Revised
69 Statutes relating to information services do not impair or affect existing agreements
70 with a federally recognized Indian tribe and that any interlocal agreement entered
71 into must respect the sovereign governance of the tribe and provide for jointly
72 agreed upon data protocols.
73 To the extent that funding is available, section 8 of this bill requires the
74 Security Operations Center, in collaboration with the Nevada System of Higher
75 Education, to develop the Cybersecurity Talent Pipeline Program.
76 Section 9 of this bill amends the definition of “information service,” as
77 provided by the Office to a using agency, to include the real-time monitoring of
78 cyberinfrastructure, threat mitigation, incident response and cybersecurity
79 enforcement.
80 Existing law makes certain legislative determinations and declarations relating
81 to the purpose of the Governor’s Technology Office. (NRS 242.071) Section 12 of
82 this bill revises these determinations and declarations to include performing
83 information services for using agencies.
84 Existing law provides that certain documents assembled, maintained, overseen
85 or prepared by the Governor’s Technology Office to mitigate, prevent or respond to
86 acts of terrorism are confidential. (NRS 242.105) Section 14 of this bill provides
87 that certain documents relating to the cybersecurity of a using agency are also
88 confidential.
89 Existing law requires the Chief to adopt certain regulations relating to
90 information systems of certain state agencies. (NRS 242.111) Section 15 of this bill
91 instead requires the Chief to adopt certain regulations relating to information
92 systems of using agencies.
93 Existing law requires the Chief to advise using agencies regarding the policy
94 for information services of the Executive Branch of Government. (NRS 242.151)
95 Section 17 of this bill requires the Chief to instead advise the using agencies of the
96 policy for information services of the Governor’s Technology Office.
97 Existing law provides that all equipment of an agency or elected state officer
98 which is owned or leased by the State must be under the managerial control of the
99 Office. (NRS 242.161) Section 18 of this bill: (1) provides instead that all
100 equipment of a using agency which is owned or leased by the State must be under
101 the managerial control of the Office; (2) prohibits the Security Operations Center
102 from assuming operational control of the equipment or software systems of a using
103 agency; and (3) requires the Security Operations Center to provide to a using
104 agency standards and policies for the equipment or software systems to be deployed
105 by the Security Operations Center, which must be agreed upon in writing before the
106 Security Operations Center provides services.
107 Section 19 of this bill provides that the Office is responsible for any application
108 of an information system which it furnishes to using agencies.
